<section class="block-section story">
  <span class="section-tag">📖 Story</span>
  <h2>Why this block matters</h2>
  <p class="sub">Last day before the Policy Panel. Final-drafting + rehearsal.</p>
  <p>The first 50 minutes is final-drafting time. Finalize all 5 sections of your <a href="/units/unit-4/assessment-chennai-climate-brief/">Brief</a>. Lock your format (written / video / infographic). Check the three rubric gates one more time: <strong>are your Recommendations specific</strong> (not "raise awareness")? Is your voice <strong>policy-brief</strong> (not academic-essay)? Is your <strong>AI Documentation specific</strong> (not "I used AI for help")?</p>
  <p>The next 25 minutes is rehearsal in pairs or trios. Practice your 4-minute pitch + answer panel-style questions. The <a href="/ai-partners/policy-aide/">Policy Aide</a>'s panel-role-play mode is the highest-value AI use today — it asks the four question categories real panels ask: cost, feasibility, equity, science credibility. The exchange you have with the Policy Aide tonight is the conversation you'll have with your peer panel tomorrow, but more comfortable to fail in.</p>
  <p>By end of class, your video-format submission is pre-recorded (if you chose that route) or you're prepped for the live panel.</p>
</section>

