<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">🛠️ Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end with a panel-ready Brief + a peer-rehearsal feedback note.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have a complete final draft of the Brief, I have rehearsed the 4-min pitch with at least one peer, and I have draft answers to at least 3 likely panel questions.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Final drafting + paired panel rehearsal (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">50 minutes drafting → 25 minutes paired panel rehearsal. Use the protocol: 4-min pitch, then partner asks 3 panel-style questions across cost / feasibility / equity / science. Switch. Each gives one specific suggestion per category.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo + pairs · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Policy Aide panel role-play (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">High-value if you have anxiety about the live panel. Open the <a href="/ai-partners/policy-aide/">Policy Aide</a>. Set it to panel-role-play mode. It will ask the four question categories. Practice the exchange 2-3 times. Document the toughest question + your final answer in your AI Doc.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pre-record video alt-format (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">For students whose video format was pre-approved with Mr. Ignash. Spend the block finalizing and recording the 6-min video submission. Submit to Classroom by end of class. Capacity for re-takes in the quiet corner.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Alt</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">4-min pitch structure peer-help (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">If you're not sure how to compress your Brief into 4 minutes, come to the peer-help table. Pair with a student who has a structured pitch. Use the Step 8 component breakdown (30/60/60/30).</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="block-section show">
  <span class="section-tag">📊 Show</span>
  <h2>What you're submitting today</h2>
  <p class="sub">Components 5 (T/T) and 6 (K/U) of the Climate Brief lock today — OPVL on 3 sources + AI Doc log. Plus: panel-ready (or alt-format submitted) + peer feedback note.</p>
  <div class="submission-callout">
    <div class="label">📥 Components 5 + 6 lock: OPVL on 3 sources + AI Documentation log. Plus: final draft + peer-rehearsal feedback note</div>
    <p>Two components lock today: <strong>Component 5 — OPVL on 3 sources</strong> (one IPCC or government source, one local/news or NGO source, one AI source — the AI source is required; each Limitation <em>specific</em> to your challenge; T/T) and <strong>Component 6 — AI Documentation log</strong> (every substantive AI conversation logged, with "one thing the AI got wrong"; K/U). With these in, K/U and T/T are essentially complete — Block 12 marks only the C strand. ALSO due (not strand-marked): either (a) your video-format submission to Classroom OR (b) your panel-ready Brief in your dossier folder, PLUS a peer-rehearsal feedback note — one specific suggestion per question category (cost / feasibility / equity / science). The peer-rehearsal note is required even if you went video-format.</p>
    <a href="#" class="rubric-link">Submit via Google Classroom →</a>
  </div>
  <p class="rubric-meta">
    <strong>Rubric link:</strong> Components 5 and 6 are the last K/U + T/T locks in the <a href="/units/unit-4/assessment-chennai-climate-brief/">rolling-summative</a> sequence. Generic Limitations ("it's not recent," "AI can hallucinate") don't clear the T/T bar; a missing or trivial AI log scores the K/U-AI-Doc component 1-2. The rest of today addresses the C strand before it locks in Block 12 — C 7-8 requires "Policy Panel Q&amp;A confident, substantive, specific," and that confidence comes from rehearsal, not improvisation. See the <a href="/foundations/the-rubric/">rubric</a>.
  </p>
</section>

